## Extension

Register callbacks in `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}Hooks` to extend abstract
actions. Abstract hooks are read-only extension points: use them to observe the
execution context or bridge to external systems, but do not mutate persistent
machine variables from inside the callback. In particular, do not write through
`{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_vars_mut(...)` or `machine->vars` in an
abstract hook.

```c
static void custom_hook(
    {{ machine_class_name(model) }} *machine,
    const {{ machine_class_name(model) }}ExecutionContext *ctx,
    void *user_data
)
{
    (void)machine;
    (void)ctx;
    (void)user_data;
}

int main(void)
{
    {{ machine_class_name(model) }} machine;
    {{ machine_class_name(model) }}Hooks hooks = {{ machine_class_name(model) | upper }}_HOOKS_INIT;

    {{ machine_class_name(model) }}_init(&machine);
